-- Italian Finance Police Seize Uni Land Shares Amid Probe Into Market Abuse
-- B y   D a n   L i e f g r e e n   a n d   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e
-- 2011-02-02T10:55:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-02/italy-seizes-uni-land-shares-probes-22-in-investigation-of-market-abuse.html
Italy’s finance police said they’re
probing 22 people and a company amid allegations of insider
trading and market manipulation, according to a statement today.  The police is seizing shares of  Uni Land SpA  and House
Building with a market value of 109 million euros, according to
the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net  